Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as 84bf73106b95a0409eb8dc3ecc3275849379d702
What is this for?  Isn't there only 1 host?
Looks like it might be set up to provide a single host with two independent serial consoles?  (Not sure though, and I'd be curious to hear the motivation...)

AMD CRBs have Physical UARTs and Virtual UARTs [eSPI/LPC]. Based on Validation needs, instead of creating separate bmc binaries, we listen on both physical UART and VUART so that based on the host configuration we capture host logs coming in on Physical UART or VUART. Port 2200 for Physical, Port 2201 for VUART. It's also true that newer CRBs will use this for multi-node scenarios.
Please retab to use 4-step spaces.
Done
I'm guessing the mode change on this file (0644->0755, i.e. making it executable) was accidental, but it certainly doesn't seem appropriate.
Not sure how it happened , will fix in the next patch.
Jayanth - is this resolved?
yes it is fixed. .
